<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 27 日星期六 03:17:37 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Super Typhoon Mawar to Become Most Powerful Storm on Earth in More Than 2 Years]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110621179" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110621297_0:0:1039:682_1440x900_80_0_1_93854795242454226e855decc65ed16c.png?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1110621279" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/super-typhoon-mawar-to-become-most-powerful-storm-on-earth-in-more-than-2-years-1110621179.html?share-img=1110621279"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://twitter.com/zoom_earth/status/1662081689382801409?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1662081689382801409%7Ctwgr%5E8a59a7354dedae99561cd2fc5b16621544f4648d%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fweather%2F2023%2F05%2F26%2Fsuper-typhoon-hurricane-mawar%2F" title="推特/@zoom_earth">Twitter/@zoom_earth</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">台风玛娃</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Typhoon Mawar  - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="台风玛娃" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110621297_0:49:1039:633_1920x0_80_0_0_bbe980a11cd79dabf60f29931f43578a.png" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110621297_0:49:1039:633_640x0_80_0_0_ae8d350ade7d4be189ac4b62f97cf1b9.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110621297_0:49:1039:633_1280x0_80_0_0_a2186714a2a2eb18a3237fcee2a9fff9.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110621297_0:49:1039:633_1920x0_80_0_0_bbe980a11cd79dabf60f29931f43578a.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://twitter.com/zoom_earth/status/1662081689382801409?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1662081689382801409%7Ctwgr%5E8a59a7354dedae99561cd2fc5b16621544f4648d%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fweather%2F2023%2F05%2F26%2Fsuper-typhoon-hurricane-mawar%2F" title="推特/@zoom_earth">推特/@zoom_earth</a> </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="ar1x1" data-source-sid="" alt=" - Sputnik International" title="" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/0b/1092187887_0:0:2048:2049_100x100_80_0_0_0c2cc4c84f89aff034cc55bb01fb6697.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">玛丽·曼利</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_manley_mary/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">周三，风暴向关岛北部移动，成为 4 级气旋。从那时起，它已升级为 5 级风暴，并有望成为 2000 年以来全球发生的十大最强风暴之一。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">预报员警告说，超级台风玛娃现在正在加速，并将成为历史上最强大的风暴之一。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">本周早些时候袭击关岛北部的风暴持续风速接近每小时 200 英里，并产生了 70 英尺高的海浪。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然风暴眼未及美国领土，但关岛仍遭遇强风和暴雨，导致其 168,000 名居民面临供水问题、破坏、可能发生的洪水和停电。<strong>风暴过后没有人员伤亡报告。</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social"><div class="ria-tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">令人惊叹的超级台风<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Mawar?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Mawar</a>继续穿越菲律宾海。预报显示台风不会袭击菲律宾。更有可能的是，Mawar 将卷土重来并削弱台湾东部。 <a href="https://t.co/96a5zDg8aw">pic.twitter.com/96a5zDg8aw</a></p> - Zoom Earth 🌎 (@zoom_earth) <a href="https://twitter.com/zoom_earth/status/1662081689382801409?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 5 月 26 日</a></blockquote></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国总统乔拜登周四晚些时候批准了该岛领土的灾难声明。到周五早上，Mawar 的风速达到了每小时 165 英里。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然该岛的台风警报于周四下午 5 点解除，但风暴仍在继续向台湾方向移动，同时保持其 5 级强度。但是，随着该系统接近东亚国家，预计该系统最终会减弱。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">风暴也可能在下周初转向日本附近。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social"><div class="ria-tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">超级台风玛娃令人惊叹的卫星图像。 <a href="https://t.co/850iZSK2JE">pic.twitter.com/850iZSK2JE</a></p> - CIRA (@CIRA_CSU) <a href="https://twitter.com/CIRA_CSU/status/1661878242020831232?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 5 月 25 日</a></blockquote></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">台风通常是在风吹入海水温暖的海洋区域时产生的，当冷空气混合在其中产生压力时，导致风移动得更快。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><u><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/weather/2023/05/26/super-typhoon-hurricane-mawar/">菲利斯</a></u>台风记录于 1958 年 5 月 29 日，是美国国家气象局数据库中的另一场西太平洋台风，风速与玛瓦一样强。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 03:02:45 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/super-typhoon-mawar-to-become-most-powerful-storm-on-earth-in-more-than-2-years-1110621179.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/super-typhoon-mawar-to-become-most-powerful-storm-on-earth-in-more-than-2-years-1110621179.html<category>超越政治</category><category>天气</category><category>极端天气</category><category>极端的天气条件</category><category>台风</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>台湾</category><category>日本</category><category>关岛</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Software Malfunction Caused April Crash of Lunar Landing Module - ispace]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110620499" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1a/1109834522_0:0:2968:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_393a119617980ed6f8c04d456361bc43.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109834504" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/software-malfunction-caused-april-crash-of-lunar-landing-module---ispace-1110620499.html?share-img=1109834504"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Ross D. Franklin</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Hakuto-R 展示其月球着陆器，该着陆器计划成为 SpaceX Falcon 9 火箭的一部分，用于 2020 年和 2021 年的任务，在 CES 上展示 1 月 6 日星期日在国际消费电子展上亮相, 2019, 在拉斯维加斯。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Hakuto-R shows off its lunar lander, which is scheduled to be part of the SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket for a 2020 and 2021 missions, shown at the CES Unveiled at CES International, Sunday, Jan. 6, 2019, in Las Vegas. - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="Hakuto-R 展示了其月球着陆器，该着陆器计划成为 SpaceX 猎鹰 9 号火箭的一部分，用于 2020 年和 2021 年的任务，该着陆器于 2019 年 1 月 6 日星期日在拉斯维加斯举行的国际消费电子展上亮相。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1a/1109834522_0:0:2968:1671_1920x0_80_0_0_d1eafcd6b3953323378079aeb15718f1.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1a/1109834522_0:0:2968:1671_640x0_80_0_0_2df51fd8899d9ff25f6463c3e7072c3f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1a/1109834522_0:0:2968:1671_1280x0_80_0_0_c28d403f7556da7d67ecf29d750b69a6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1a/1109834522_0:0:2968:1671_1920x0_80_0_0_d1eafcd6b3953323378079aeb15718f1.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Ross D. Franklin </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">日本的 ispace 早些时候详细说明，在官方与着陆器失去联系后，它为纪念首次私人登陆地球卫星而做出的努力没有成功。当时的初步细节表明，该船意外加速进入月球表面。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> ispace 进行的一项调查证实，软件故障是日本 ispace Hakuto-R Mission 1 着陆器上个月在尝试登月时坠毁的原因。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该公司于周五召开新闻发布会宣布完成分析。 Hakuto-R Mission 1 着陆器成功执行了计划的着陆顺序，逐渐减速至大约每小时 2 英里的速度。它仍然在月球表面上方约三英里处。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，在耗尽燃料后，航天器以超过每小时 200 英里的速度<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230426/japans-hakuto-r-module-likely-miscalculated-sped-up-moments-before-lunar-crash-1109864387.html" target="_blank">坠</a>入阿特拉斯陨石坑。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social" data-social="youtube"><div class="article__youtube"><iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Owt2u9SJIbU" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitAllowFullScreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" allowfullscreen="allowFullScreen" frameborder="0" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国宇航局通过发布其月球勘测轨道器拍摄的照片为调查做出了贡献，这些照片拍摄了坠机现场的照片。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">硬件还是软件？</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">调查显示，负责引导下降的软件在越过月球表面一个比周围地形高约两英里的陨石坑边缘时失去了对着陆器高度的追踪。该软件错误地确定高度传感器发生故障并忽略了准确的高度测量。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">幸运的是，检查确定航天器的其他硬件组件按预期运行，表明整体设计的可靠性。现在的重点是纠正软件问题，这通常比重大的硬件检修更容易管理。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> ispace 的首席技术官 Ryo Ujiie 在周五的新闻发布会上强调，故障不是由于硬件故障造成的，因此无需在这方面进行修改。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管航天器的着陆软件是由马萨诸塞州剑桥市的德雷珀实验室开发的，但 ispace 对坠机负责，因为该软件是为满足公司要求而编写的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">不当的改变？</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">坠机事件也至少部分归因于 ispace 在 2021 年初完成航天器设计后决定改变着陆点。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Lacus Somniorum 是一个平坦的平原，最初被选为登陆点；然而，该公司后来选择了 Atlas，这是一个直径超过 50 英里的大型撞击坑，认为它是一个更迷人的目的地。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110620499" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110620771_0:0:1100:1100_1440x900_80_0_1_a05a3326f946ebcc6e57d6a8a06b7313.png?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110620753" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/software-malfunction-caused-april-crash-of-lunar-landing-module---ispace-1110620499.html?share-img=1110620753"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片： <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-s-lro-views-impact-site-of-hakuto-r-mission-1-moon-lander" title="美国宇航局戈达德太空飞行中心/亚利桑那州立大学">美国宇航局戈达德太空飞行中心/亚利桑那州立大学</a>/</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">HAKUTO-R Mission 1 月球着陆器站点，如 2023 年 4 月 26 日月球勘测轨道器相机 (LROC) 所见，即尝试着陆后的第二天。比例尺横跨 100 m。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="HAKUTO-R Mission 1 lunar lander site, as seen by the Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter Camera (LROC) on April 26, 2023, the day after the attempted landing. The scale bar is 100 m across. - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="2023 年 4 月 26 日，也就是尝试着陆后的第二天，月球勘测轨道器相机 (LROC) 看到的 HAKUTO-R Mission 1 月球着陆器站点。比例尺横跨 100 m。" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110620771_0:0:1100:1100_1920x0_80_0_0_d83d10b6fd006f63c12578e7d4b3c46c.png" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221920%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1920" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110620771_0:0:1100:1100_640x0_80_0_0_58a4bfbf052eb0053c5914c2c9ce6aaa.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110620771_0:0:1100:1100_1280x0_80_0_0_2b0ffde62dec91cde1d4bd0d4328568b.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110620771_0:0:1100:1100_1920x0_80_0_0_d83d10b6fd006f63c12578e7d4b3c46c.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet=""> 2023 年 4 月 26 日，也就是尝试着陆后的第二天，月球勘测轨道器相机 (LROC) 看到的 HAKUTO-R Mission 1 月球着陆器站点。比例尺横跨 100 m。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片： <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-s-lro-views-impact-site-of-hakuto-r-mission-1-moon-lander" title="美国宇航局戈达德太空飞行中心/亚利桑那州立大学">美国宇航局戈达德太空飞行中心/亚利桑那州立大学</a>/ </div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">因此，着陆软件没有足够的设备来处理航天器经过陨石坑边缘后的高度变化。在模拟过程中没有发现这种疏忽。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">月球前景</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">ispace 的创始人兼首席执行官 Takeshi Hakamada 宣布，该公司即将执行的任务大部分不受坠机事件的影响。该公司计划在明年推出一个几乎相同的着陆器，并计划在 2025 年将一个更大的航天器发射到月球的远端。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Hakamada 对公司根据从这次失败中获得的洞察力加强未来任务的能力表示了信心。他还提到该公司已经为着陆器购买了保险，将财务影响降至最低，估计损失约为 710,000 美元。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “我们对如何改进我们未来的任务有非常清晰的认识，”袴田说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110620499" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/software-malfunction-caused-april-crash-of-lunar-landing-module---ispace-1110620499.html?share-block=1110621125" data-title="&amp;quot;We have a very clear picture of how to improve our future missions,&amp;quot; Hakamada said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">展望未来，其他几艘航天器计划于今年晚些时候发射到月球。根据美国宇航局的一项计划，该计划涉及与私营公司合作，将科学仪器运送到月球表面。匹兹堡的 Astrobotic Technology 和休斯顿的 Intuitive Machines 将在未来几个月内将<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20190828/nasa-offers-7-billion-in-contracts-to-accelerate-work-towards-2024-moon-landing-target--1076661262.html" target="_blank">各自的航天器</a>送上月球。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，印度航天局最近宣布了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20200101/india-approves-third-lunar-mission-chandrayaan-3-isro-chief-reveals-1077913557.html" target="_blank">Chandrayaan-3</a>计划，这是其 2019 年登月失败尝试的后续任务，发射日期最早可能在 7 月 12 日。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 02:53:22 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/software-malfunction-caused-april-crash-of-lunar-landing-module---ispace-1110620499.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/software-malfunction-caused-april-crash-of-lunar-landing-module---ispace-1110620499.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>日本</category><category>月亮</category><category>月球任务</category><category>登月任务</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kiev Disrupts Rotation of IAEA Staff at Zaporozhye Nuclear Plant - Regional Authorities]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110620617" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18881/06/188810638_0:0:3086:2000_1440x900_80_0_1_a3d889567d68e128463a4da18206bb5c.jpg?source-sid=rian0_photo" data-photoview-image-id="188810634" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/kiev-disrupts-rotation-of-iaea-staff-at-zaporozhye-nuclear-plant---regional-authorities-1110620617.html?share-img=188810634"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© RIA Novosti</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">乌克兰扎波罗热核电站</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian0_photo" alt="The Zaporozhye nuclear power plant, Ukraine - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="乌克兰扎波罗热核电站" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18881/06/188810638_0:132:3087:1868_1920x0_80_0_0_52050cdee1168bc92af9cd989616e9dd.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18881/06/188810638_0:132:3087:1868_640x0_80_0_0_76a81af2f262304b1d7cc77a179957c8.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18881/06/188810638_0:132:3087:1868_1280x0_80_0_0_14f210fc573cd4880a5271eaa34c145f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18881/06/188810638_0:132:3087:1868_1920x0_80_0_0_52050cdee1168bc92af9cd989616e9dd.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 俄新社</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">SIMFEROPOL（人造卫星）网：扎波罗热地区政府高级官员弗拉基米尔·罗戈夫告诉人造卫星网，基辅当局扰乱了扎波罗热核电站（ZNPP）国际原子能机构（IAEA）工作人员的轮换。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自 2022 年 9 月以来，原子能机构工作组一直在 ZNPP。自那时以来，原子能机构共进行了七次工作人员轮换，最后一次轮换已于 4 月底完成。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">罗戈夫说：“最初，轮换应该在 5 月 25 日进行，然后应基辅的要求，推迟到 26 日，结果被乌克兰方面打乱了。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110620617" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/kiev-disrupts-rotation-of-iaea-staff-at-zaporozhye-nuclear-plant---regional-authorities-1110620617.html?share-block=1110620619" data-title="&quot;Initially, the rotation was supposed to take place on May 25, then, at the request of Kiev, it was postponed to the 26 and, as a result, was disrupted by the Ukrainian side,&quot; Rogov said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位高级官员具体指出，三名国际原子能机构视察员应该抵达 ZNPP：来自阿根廷、爱尔兰和摩洛哥。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “在 [IAEA] 任务抵达前夕，[乌克兰总统 Volodymyr] Zelensky 的政权下令对 Vasylivka 市进行大规模重型武器炮击，Vasylivka 市是监测任务通常经过的路线，”罗戈夫告诉人造卫星。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">瑞士外交部发言人尼古拉斯·比多周四告诉卫星通讯社，联合国安理会计划于 5 月 30 日召开会议，讨论扎波罗热核电站的安全问题。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">扎波罗热核电站位于第聂伯河左岸，是欧洲单机数量和能量输出最大的核电站。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年 3 月上旬，在俄罗斯的特别军事行动期间，ZNPP 被俄罗斯控制。它曾多次遭到乌克兰炮击，引发了国际社会对发生核事故可能性的担忧。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 01:57:40 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/kiev-disrupts-rotation-of-iaea-staff-at-zaporozhye-nuclear-plant---regional-authorities-1110620617.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/kiev-disrupts-rotation-of-iaea-staff-at-zaporozhye-nuclear-plant---regional-authorities-1110620617.html<category>世界</category><category>扎波罗热核电站</category><category>谢尔盖·罗戈夫</category><category>基辅</category><category>国际原子能机构 (IAEA)</category></item></channel></rss>